In a press briefing, White House Deputy Press Secretary Raj Shah addressed the allegations of domestic abuse made against former White House staff secretary Rob Porter. Shah explained the background investigation process that is conducted for White House staffers and emphasized that the investigation was ongoing at the time of Porter's resignation. Shah stated that the allegations against Porter were taken seriously and investigated as part of the background check process. He also mentioned that the President was surprised and saddened by the allegations. Shah declined to provide specific details about when the White House became aware of the allegations or whether Chief of Staff John Kelly was fully aware of the situation. Shah also addressed other topics during the briefing, such as the budget deal, the stock market volatility, and North Korea.